column12: PERFUME-FREE TWO PHASE COMPOSITIONS AND METHODS FOR REDUCING BODY AND ENVIRONMENTAL ODOR
column13: The present invention relates to an aqueous odor-absorbing composition which is safe for use on human skin comprising solubilized, water-soluble, uncomplexed cyclodextrin; an oil phase selected from the group consisting of emollients, moisturizers, skin protectants, and mixtures thereof; one or more surfactants each having hydrophilic/lipophilic balance of about 8-18, and wherein each surfactant, when combined with an aqueous cyclodextrin solution, provides no less than about 25 % a level of odor capture as an aqueous cyclodextrin solution; and an aqueous carrier. The present invention also encompasses methods of controlling body and environmental odors on skin comprising the application to skin of these compositions.

column12: Vücut kokusunun düsürülmesi için parfümlü bir ve iki fazli bilesimler ve bu bilesimlerin kullanim yöntemleri.
column13: Bu bulus, koku sogurucu bilesimler ve bunlarin deri üzerinde kullanimina iliskindir. Bilesimler, bilesimin agirligi ile %0.1-5 kadar çözündürülmüs, suda çözünür, komplekslenmemis siklodekstrini; bilesimin agirligi ile %0.004-2 kadar bir parfüm bilesimini; ve bir sulu tasiyici maddeyi içermektedir. Bilesimler, ayni zamanda, ya düsük molekül agirlikli bir dimetikon ya da yumusaticilar, nemlendiriciler, deri koruyucular ve bunlarin karisimlarindan seçilen bir yag fazini ve bir ya da daha çok sürfaktani içerebilmektedir. Bu bulusun koku sogurucu bilesimleri, ayni zamanda, tercihan, suda çözünür ve/veya hidrofobik antimikrobik maddelerin etkili bir miktarini da ihtiva edebilmektedir. Bu bulus, ayni zamanda bir bükülgen dagitma araci üzerinde biriktirilmis koku sogurucu bilesimlere de iliskindir.

column12: METHODS AND COMPOSITIONS FOR REDUCING BODY ODOR
column13: The present invention relates to an odor absorbing composition, which is safe for use on human skin, comprising from 0.1 % to 5 %, by weight of the composition, of solubilized, water-soluble, uncomplexed cyclodextrin; from 0.1 % to 36 %, by weight of the composition, of an oil phase selected from the group consisting of emollients, moisturizers, and skin protectants; an emulsifier; and an aqueous carrier. The odor absorbing compositions of the present invention may also contain an effective amount of hydrophobic antimicrobials. The present invention also relates to the use of cyclodextrin-containing compositions for the manufacture of an odor absorbing composition, which is safe for use on skin, for controlling environmental malodors on skin and for reducing body odor and/or vaginal odor.
column15: TRINH TOAN;;DODD MICHAEL THOMAS;;BARTOLO ROBERT GREGORY;;LUCAS JULIET MARIE;;BUCKNER ROBIN YAGER;;KAJS THERESA MARIE

column12: Parfymefrie to-fase blandinger og fremgangsmåter for å redusere kropps- og omgivelseslukt
column13: Foreliggende oppfinnelse gjelder en vandig luktabsorberende blanding som er sikker til bruk på menneskelig hud, omfattende løseliggjort, vannløselig, ikke-komplekst syklo- dekstrin; en oljefase valgt fra gruppen bestående av myk- gjørere, fuktemidler, hudbeskyttende midler, og blandinger av disse; et eller flere overflateaktive stoff som hver har en hydrofil/ lipofil balanse på ca 8-18, og hvori hvert overflateaktivt stoff, når det kombineres med en vandig syklodekstrinløsning, gir ikke mindre enn 25% av luktfang- sten som en vandig syklodekstrin og en vandig bærer. Fore- liggende oppfinnelse innbefatter også metoder til å kontrollere kroppslukt og omgivende lukt på huden og omfatter appliseringen på huden av disse blandingene.

column12: Methods using uncomplexed cyclodextrin solutions for controlling environmental odors
column13: The present invention encompasses methods of controlling environmental malodors on human skin comprising the application to the skin of a composition comprising from about 0.1% to about 5%, by weight of the composition, of solubilized, water-soluble, uncomplexed cyclodextrin; and an aqueous carrier. The compositions can also comprise one or more of the following optional components: a linear dimethicone having a nominal viscosity of about 350 ecentistokes or less; low molecular weight polyols; water-soluble antimicrobial preservatives; zinc salts; water-soluble polymers; soluble carbonate and/or bicarbonate salts; chelating agents; zeolites; activated carbon; and mixtures thereof. The compositions can be applied directly as a spray, poured from a bottle and applied by hand, or applied via a wipe.

column12: Perfume-free two phase compositions for reducing body odor
column13: The present invention relates to a perfume-free odor absorbing composition, which is safe for use on skin comprising from about 0.1% to about 5%, by weight of the composition, of solubilized, water-soluble, uncomplexed cyclodextrin; from about 0.1% to about 36%, by weight of the composition, of an oil phase selected from the group consisting of emollients, moisturizers, skin protectants, and mixtures thereof; one or more surfactants each having a hydrophilic/lipophilic balance of about 8-18, and wherein each surfactant, when combined with an aqueous cyclodextrin solution, provides no less than about 25% a level of odor capture as an aqueous cyclodextrin solution; and an aqueous carrier. The odor absorbing compositions of the present invention may also contain an effective amount of hydrophobic antimicrobials.

column12: MULTI-PHASIC IMPLANT DEVICE FOR THE REPAIR OR REPLACEMENT OF CARTILAGE TISSUE
column13: Tissue implants prepared for the repair of tissues, especially avascular tissues such as cartilage. One embodiment presents an electric potential capable of receiving and accumulating desirable factors or molecules from surrounding fluid when exposed to dynamic loading. In another embodiment the implant promotes tissue conduction by retarding, restricting and controlling cellular invasion through use of gradients until competent tissue forms. Further embodiments of the tissue implants may be formed into a multi-phasic device that provides deep tissue mechanical stimulus by conduction of mechanical and fluid forces experienced at the surface of the implant.

column12: Methods and compositions for reducing body odor
column13: The present invention relates to an aqueous, odor absorbing composition, which is safe for use on human skin comprising from about 0.1% to about 5%, by weight of the composition, of solubilized, water-soluble, uncomplexed cyclodextrin; from about 0.5% to about 30%, by weight of the composition, of a linear dimethicone having a nominal viscosity of about 350 centistokes or less; and an aqueous carrier. column12: Systems and methods for automatic submission, audit and adjustment of mortgage insurance claims
column13: Systems and methods are described for automatically processing mortgage insurance claims. In one described system, a central server computer receives inputs from, and provides outputs to, a servicer terminal connected into a network. The servicer terminal captures data from a servicer submitting a mortgage insurance claim. A claims database is connected into the network, containing data relating to the mortgage insurance claim. A claim audit rulebase is connected into the network, for automatically performing an audit and adjustment of the submitted mortgage insurance claim. The system automatically provides results of the audit and adjustment to the servicer at the servicer terminal, and presents the servicer with an option to interact with a claim representative to resolve any issues.

column12: Multi-phasic implant device for the repair or replacement of cartilage tissue
column13: Tissue implants prepared for the repair of tissues, especially avascular tissues such as cartilage. One embodiment presents an electric potential capable of receiving and accumulating desirable factors or molecules from surrounding fluid when exposed to dynamic loading. In another embodiment the implant promotes tissue conduction by retarding, restricting and controlling cellular invasion through use of gradients until competent tissue forms. Further embodiments of the tissue implants may be formed into a multi-phasic device that provides deep tissue mechanical stimulus by conduction of mechanical and fluid forces experienced at the surface of the implant.

N-Acylated 1-(2,3,4,5-Tetrahydro-5-oxo-2-furyl, -thienyl or -pyrrolyl)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro- or 3,4-dihydroisoquinoline derivatives of formula (I), in racemate or pure optical isomer form, are new. Z' = O, S, NH-N-alkyl or N-Boc; R' = H or OMe, or Z' + R' = OCH2O; R'' = H or Me; X = CO, SO2 or COO, and R = alkyl, aryl, alkenyl or aralkyl. An Independent claim is included for the preparation of (I).

column12: Ink jet printhead
column13: An ink jet printhead includes a printhead substrate having a plurality of thin film layers and four side by side columnar arrays of drop generators formed in the printhead substrate and extending along a longitudinal extent. Each columnar array has drop generators that are separated by a drop generator pitch P. The drop generators produce ink drops having a drop volume that enables single pass printing of a resolution that is 1/(4P) dpi along a print axis parallel to the longitudinal extent. Four columnar arrays of FET drive circuits formed in the printhead substrate are employed to energize corresponding columnar arrays of drop generators.

column12: CABEZA IMPRESORA DE CHORRO DE TINTA ESTRECHO.
column13: Una cabeza impresora de chorro de tinta, que comprende: un sustrato de cabeza de impresión (11) que incluye una pluralidad de capas de película delgadas; cuatro disposiciones en columnas (61), una al lado de otra, de generadores de gotas (40) formados en dicho sustrato de cabeza impresora y que se extienden a lo largo de una extensión longitudinal; cada disposición en columnas de generadores de gotas tiene al menos 100 generadores de gotas separados por una distancia P entre generadores de gotas; dichas cuatro disposiciones en columnas de generadores de gotas comprenden una primera disposición en columnas y una segunda disposición en columnas separadas entre sí por al menos 630 micrómetros, y una tercera disposición en columnas y una cuarta disposición en columnas separadas entre sí por como máximo 630 micrómetros; dichos generadores de gotas para producir gotas de tinta del mismo color predeterminado y con un volumen de gotas que permite una impresión de un solo color en un único paso de una resolución que es 1/(4P) dpi a lo largo de un eje de impresión paralelo a dicha extensión longitudinal; y cuatro disposiciones en columnas (81) de circuitos de excitación FET (85) formados en dicho sustrato de cabeza impresora respectivamente contigua a dichas disposiciones en columnas de generadores de gotas para energizar dichas disposiciones en columnas de generadores de gotas.

column12: COMPACT PRINTING HEAD FOR INK-JET PRINTING
column13: FIELD: printing industry; ink-jet printing. ^ SUBSTANCE: proposed printing head for ink-jet printing is provided with printing head backing including great number of fine-film layers, four matrix-columns of droplet generator arranged side-by-side which are formatted in said backing of printing head and arranged longitudinal. Said printing head contains excitation circuits which are also formed in said backing to excite each generator of ink droplets at frequency in range approximately from 15 kHz to 18 kHz, and first ink feed slot, second ink feed slot. Backing of printing head has density of ink droplet generator equal to at least 10.43 ink droplet generators per square millimeter. First matrix-column of droplet generators and second matrix-column of droplet generators are arranged from each of two sides of said first ink-feed slot, and third matrix-column of droplet generators and fourth matrix-column of droplet generators are arranged at two sides of second ink-feed slot. ^ EFFECT: provision of compact printing head with great number of ink droplet generators. ^ 33 cl, 11 dwg

column12: NARROW INK JET PRINTHEAD
column13: A narrow ink jet printhead having four columnar arrays of ink drop generators configured for monochrome single-pass printing at a print resoluion having a media axis dot spacing that is less than the columnar nozzle spacing of the ink drop generators. column12: Zündverteiler für einen Motor mit Laserzündung
column13: Es wird ein Zündverteiler für einen lasergezündeten Mehrzylinder-Verbrennungsmotor beschrieben. Der Zündverteiler umfasst eine durch den Motor drehbare Welle 12 und mehrere ebene reflektierende Flächen 16a bis 16d an der Welle 12. Die Flächen 16a bis 16d liegen in Ebenen senkrecht zur Drehachse der Welle 12 und sind entlang der Länge der Welle axial versetzt. Ein optischer Sender 18 lenkt Licht von einer Laserquelle, so dass es bei einem Winkel der Reihe nach auf den reflektierenden Flächen 16a bis 16d auftritt, wenn die Welle 12 dreht, und mehrere voneinander beabstandete optische Empfänger 24a bis 24d empfangen jeweils das von einer jeweiligen der Spiegelflächen reflektierte Licht und lenken das reflektierte Licht zu einem jeweiligen der Motorzylinder.

column12: Duplex glass preforms for hermetic glass-to-metal compression sealing
column13: A duplex glass preform for forming hermetic glass-to-metal seals of the compression type. The duplex glass preform comprises a glass infrasturcture or matrix having at least one end thereof modified by the selective distribution therein of ceramic particles. The ceramic particles are selectively distributed to form a ceramic density gradient having the largest concentration of ceramic particles at the surface and gradually decreasing with depth. The duplex glass preform of the present invention has utility in forming glass-to-metal compression seals in hybrid metal packages containing microcircuit chips. The duplex glass preform may be used in the normal insulative fashion or as a conductive member.

column12: Distributor for engine with laser ignition
column13: A distributor is described for a multi-cylinder laser ignited internal combustion engine. The distributor comprises a shaft 12 rotatable by the engine and a plurality of flat reflective surfaces 16a to 16d on the shaft 12. The surfaces 16a to 16d lie in planes normal to the axis of rotation of the shaft 12 and are axially staggered from one another along the length of the shaft. An optical transmitter 18 directs light from a laser source to impinge at an angle sequentially on the reflective surfaces 16a to 16d as the shaft 12 rotates, and a plurality of optical receivers 24a to 24d spaced from one another each receive the light reflected from a respective one of the mirror surfaces and direct the reflected light to a respective one of the engine cylinders.

column12: EXECUTIVE DEVICE OF AEROSOL CYLINDER WITH CHILD SAFE LOCK
column13: FIELD: aerosols; safe locks.SUBSTANCE: invention relates to an actuator of an aerosol can with protection against opening by children for use with a container of a fluid medium under pressure. The actuator includes a casing configured to be located on the aerosol container above the rod, and an executive element mounted on the casing and made with the ability to move in it to ensure that the rod is pressed by applying an external force applied to the upper surface of the executive element. The actuator includes a nozzle and a channel for connecting the stem and nozzle. The cap is normally positioned to block the movement of the actuator to push the stem. The blocking element normally crosses the path of movement of the cap with the possibility of blocking the cap in its locked position. The blocking element has two sections, both of which must be simultaneously moved to a position located at a distance from the path of movement of the cap, as a result of which the cap can be moved from its locked position, with the provision of movement of the actuator to push the stem.EFFECT: efficient child protection lock.71 cl, 9 dwg
column15: STARZMAN MICHAEL J;;FREUDENBERG JOHN W;;BATES KEVIN VICTOR;;KRUPP BENJAMIN THOMAS;;STATES ROBERT GERALD;;PARROTT DAVID A;;GOOD ROBERT J;;DODD JOSEPH K;;FALCON SARA DAWSON

column12: Child resistant aerosol actuator
column13: The actuator includes a shroud adapted to be situated on an aerosol container over the stem and an actuation member mounted on and moveable within the shroud to depress the stem by the application of an external force applied to the top surface of the actuation member. The actuation member includes a nozzle and a conduit for connecting the stem and the nozzle. A hood is normally positioned to block the actuation member from being moved to depress the stem. A locking member normally intersects the path of movement of the hood to lock the hood in its blocking position. The locking member has two sections both of which must be simultaneously moved to a position remote from the path of hood movement such that the hood may be moved from its blocking position, allowing the actuation member to be moved to depress the stem.

column12: acionador de aerossol resistente a crianças
column13: a presente invenção refere-se a um acionador que inclui uma cobertura adaptada para ser situada em um recipiente aerossol sobre a haste e um membro de acionamento montado em e móvel dentro da cobertura para pressionar a haste pela aplicação de uma força externa aplicada na superfície de topo do membro de acionamento. o membro de acionamento inclui um bocal e um conduto para conectar a haste e o bocal. a cobertura de proteção é normalmente posicionada para impedir que o membro de acionamento seja movido para pressionar a haste. um membro de travamento normalmente intersecta o trajeto de movimento da cobertura de proteção para travar a cobertura de proteção em sua posição de bloqueio. o membro de travamento tem duas seções ambas as quais devem ser simultaneamente movidas para uma posição remota a partir do trajeto de movimento da cobertura de proteção de modo que a cobertura de proteção pode ser movida a partir de sua posição de bloqueio, permitindo que o membro de acionamento seja movido para pressionar a haste.

column12: COMPUESTOS Y COMPOSICIONES PARA INHIBIR LA ACTIVIDAD DE LA ABL1, ABL2 Y BCR-ABL1
column13: Compuestos capaces de inhibir la actividad de BCR-ABL1 y mutantes de los mismos. Además se proporciona un proceso para la preparación de compuestos de la presente, preparaciones farmacéuticas que comprenden tales compuestos y métodos de utilizar tales compuestos en el tratamiento de cánceres. ABL Tirosina quinasa de la proteína de Abelson. Reivindicación 1: El compuesto de la reivindicación 1 de la fórmula (1) en el cual R¹ es pirazolilo; en donde dicho pirazolilo es sustituido o no sustituido con 1 a 2 grupos R⁶; R² es pirrolidinilo; en donde dicho pirrolidinilo es sustituido por un grupo R⁷; R³ se selecciona a partir de hidrógeno y halo; R⁴ se selecciona a partir de -SF₅ y -Y²-CF₂-Y³; R⁶ en cada ocurrencia es independientemente seleccionado a partir de hidrógeno, hidroxilo, metilo, metoxilo, ciano, trifluorometilo, hidroxi- metilo, halo, amino, fluoro-etilo, etilo y ciclopropilo; R⁷ se selecciona a partir de hidroxilo, metilo, halo, metoxilo, hidroxilo-metilo, amino, metilo-amino, amino-metilo, trifluorometilo, 2-hidroxipropan-2-ilo, metilocarbonil-amino, dimetil-amino, 2-amino-3-metilbutanoil)oxilo, carboxilo, metoxilo-carbonilo, fosfonooxilo, ciano y amino-carbonilo; Y se selecciona a partir de CH y N; Y¹ se selecciona a partir de CH y N; Y² se selecciona a partir de CF₂, O y S(O)₀₋₂; e Y³ se seleccionado a partir de hidrógeno, cloro, flúor, metilo, difluorometilo y trifluorometilo; o las sales farmacéuticamente aceptables de los mismos.

column12: Compounds and compositions for inhibiting the activity of ABL1, ABL2 and BCR-ABL1

column12: Dip tube connectors and pump systems using the same
column13: A pump system may include a blown-in dip tube connected to a valve body and having a connection which may include an improved blown-in dip tube connector having one or more of a lip for sealing with a blown-in dip tube, a seal ring configured to mate with a blown-in dip tube and seal therewith, a dip tube lock for mating with a blown-in dip tube, or an O-ring for providing an improved seal with a blown-in dip tube.

column12: Systems and Methods for Collection and Automatic Analysis of Opinions on Various Types of Media
column13: Systems and methods for collection and automatic analysis of opinions of media are provided. A representative method includes: receiving, from a user, media for review; automatically distributing the media to a pool of reviewers based on reviewer profiles; receiving, from the reviewers, information corresponding to opinions pertaining to the media; automatically generating a report based, at least in part, on the information received from the reviewers; and providing the report to the user.

column12: DERIVADOS DE BENZAMIDA PARA LA INHIBICION DE LA ACTIVIDAD ABL1, ABL2 Y BCR-ABL1
column13: La presente invencion se refiere a compuestos derivados de benzamida de formula (I) o sales farmaceuticamente aceptables de los mismos, donde: R1 es pirazolilo opcionalmente sustituido con 1 a 2 grupos R6; R2 es pirrolidinilo sustituido con R7; R3 es H o halogeno; R4 es -SF5 o -Y2-CF2-Y3; R6 es H, hidroxilo, entre otros; R7 es hidroxilo, metilo, entre otros; Y e Y1 son CH o N; Y2 es CF2, -O- o S(O)0-2; Y3 es H, cloro, entre otros. Es un compuesto preferido: (R)-N-(4-(cloro-difluoro-metoxi)-fenil)-6-(3-hidroxi-pirrolidin-1-il)-5-(1H-pirazol-5-il)-nicotinamida, entre otros. Tambien se refiere a una composicion farmaceutica. Dichos compuestos inhiben la actividad enzimatica de cinasa de tirosina de la proteina de Abelson: ABL1, ABL2 y la proteina quimerica BCR-ABL1, siendo utiles en el tratamiento del cancer

column12: ROTARY MILL
column13: A rotary mill is disclosed comprising a body portion ( 4 ) having a milling surface ( 10 ) and a central bore ( 20 ) extending along an axis of rotation ( 18 ) of the body portion ( 4 ); and a guide portion ( 6 ) having a guide body ( 22 ) and a guide peg ( 24 ) extending from the guide body ( 22 ), the guide peg ( 24 ) operable to be received in the central bore ( 20 ) of the body portion ( 4 ), the guide body ( 22 ) having at least one alignment feature ( 28, 30 ) which is the same as that of a prosthesis component. A method of implanting a unicondylar femoral component is also disclosed, the method comprising, a) reaming the femoral condylar surface to accept the unicondylar femoral component; b) drilling peg holes for affixing the unicondylar femoral component; c) affixing a guide portion of a rotary mill onto the prepared condylar surface using the drilled peg holes; d) reaming a portion of bone anterior to the affixed guide portion; e) removing the guide portion from the bone; and f) affixing a unicondylar femoral component to the prepared condylar surface.

column12: Digital optical network architecture
column13: A digital optical network (DON) is a new approach to low-cost, more compact optical transmitter modules and optical receiver modules for deployment in optical transport networks (OTNs). One important aspect of a digital optical network is the incorporation in these modules of transmitter photonic integrated circuit (TxPIC) chips and receiver photonic integrated circuit (TxPIC) chips in lieu of discrete modulated sources and detector sources with discrete multiplexers or demultiplexers.

column12: DIGITAL OPTICAL NETWORK ARCHITECTURE
column13: A digital optical network (DON) is a new approach to low-cost, more compact optical transmitter modules and optical receiver modules for deployment in optical transport networks (OTNs). One important aspect of a digital optical network is the incorporation in these modules of transmitter photonic integrated circuit (TxPIC) chips and receiver photonic integrated circuit (TxPIC) chips in lieu of discrete modulated sources and detector sources wit h discrete multiplexers or demultiplexers.

A képletben R1 8-18 szénatomosalkil-, alkenil-, aril-, alkilaril-, éter- vagy glicitil-éter-csoport;R2 1-3 szénatomos alkilcsoport; R3 és R4 egymástól függetlenülhidrogénatom, metil- vagy etilcsoport; A 1-4 szénatomos alkoxicsoport;X anion és p értéke 2-30 egész szám. A találmány tárgya továbbá a 2illatanyagok vagy illatkomponensek textíliákon való lerakódásánakfokozására szolgáló eljárás.

column12: LAUNDRY SYSTEM HAVING UNITIZED DOSING
column13: Compositions, articles and methods are provided for supplying fabric care benefits to clothing or fabrics in an automated washing machine and by manual washing. The fabric care compositions preferably have less than about 5% detergent surfactants, more preferably less than 3%, even more preferably less than 1% and are most preferably free of detergent surfactants. Similarly, the fabric care compositions preferably have less than about 5% fabric softener actives, more preferably less than 3%, even more preferably less than 1% and are most preferably free of detergent surfactants. The laundry articles can take a variety of forms in a variety of physical states all of which will rapidly dispense a unitized amount of one or more selected fabric care agents to a wash and/or rinse bath solution during the laundering process under a variety of conditions. The invention also pertains to laundry kits that contain a variety of such articles and instructions concerning their use. Likewise, methods for preparing a customized laundry solution to obtain a specific fabric care benefit selected based on the user's personal preferences and/or the fabric care needs of the fabrics being laundered are also provided. Further, the present invention also concerns methods for assisting a consumer in identifying the unitized articles to be used in preparing a laundry solution that will impart desired fabric care benefits as well as merchandising displays for dispensing the articles, assembling customized laundry kits and instructing the consumer on the selection and use of laundry articles.

column12: DETERGENT COMPOSITION AND ITS USE
column13: A composition comprises or is prepared by combining a soil dispersant polymer, a non alkoxylated quaternary ammonium surfactant and an alkoxylated quaternary ammonium surfactant of formula (I): (R1)(R2)N+(ApR4)(R3) (I) R1 = substituted 8-18C alkyl, alkenyl, aryl, alkaryl, ether or glycidyl ether moiety; R2 = 1-3C alkyl; R3, R4 = H, Me or Et; X = anion; A = 1-4C alkoxy; and p = 2-30. Also claimed are: (1) a method for removing soils and stains; and (2) a method for enhancing the deposition or substantivity of perfume or perfume ingredients onto fabrics or other surfaces comprising contacting the surfaces with perfume of perfume ingredient in the presence of compound (I).

column12: LAUNDRY SYSTEM HAVING UNITIZED DOSING
column13: The present invention is directed to compositions, articles and methods for supplying fabric care benefits such as, improved cleaning, to clothing or fabrics in an automated washing machine and by manual washing. The fabric care compositions preferably have less than about 5% detergent surfactants, more preferably less than 3%, even more preferably less than 1% and are most preferably free of detergent surfactants. Similarly, the fabric care compositions preferably have less than about 5% fabric softener actives, more preferably less than 3%, even more preferably less than 1% and are most preferably free of detergent surfactants. The laundry articles can take a variety of forms in a variety of physical states all of which will rapidly dispense a unitized amount of one or more selected fabric care agents to a wash and/or rinse bath solution during the laundering process under a variety of conditions. The invention also pertains to laundry kits that contain a variety of such articles and instructions concerning their use. Likewise, methods for preparing a customized laundry solution to obtain a specific fabric care benefit selected based on the user's personal preferences and/or the fabric care needs of the fabrics being laundered are also provided. Further, the present invention also concerns methods for assisting a consumer in identifying the unitized articles to be used in preparing a laundry solution that will impart desired fabric care benefits as well as merchandising displays for dispensing the articles, assembling customized laundry kits and instructing the consumer on the selection and use of laundry articles.

column12: DETERGENT COMPOSITION
column13: A detergent composition comprises or is prepared by combining a peroxygen bleach, a bleach activator, a non-alkoxylated quaternary ammonium (non-AQA) surfactant and an AQA cationic surfactant of formula (I) R1 = substituted 8-18C alkyl, alkenyl, aryl, alkaryl, ether or glycidyl ether moiety; R2 = 1-3C alkyl; R3, R4 = H, Me or Et; X = anion; A = 1-4C alkoxy; p = 2-30. Also claimed are: (1) a method for removing soils and stains comprising contacting soils and stains with a detergent composition, or aqueous medium comprising the above detergent composition; and (2) a method for enhancing the deposition or substantivity of perfume or perfume ingredients onto fabrics or other surfaces comprising contacting the surfaces with perfume of perfume ingredient in the presence of compound (I). Use - The composition is useful for removing a variety of soils, especially hydrophobic soils, bleach sensitive soils, greasy soils or surfactant sensitive soils and stains from a variety of fabrics. The composition is in the form of granules, bar, aqueous liquid or non-aqueous liquid or tablet form. Advantage - The compositions provide superior cleaning and whiteness and also provide improved fabric care. The AQA surfactants are compatible with anionic surfactants, and perfume ingredients. The compositions can be formulated as concentrates and provide economic advantage in transportation/storage costs.

Similarly, the fabric care compositions preferably have less than about 5% fabric softener actives, more preferably less than 3%, even more preferably less than 1% and are most preferably free of detergent surfactants. The laundry articles can take a variety of forms in a variety of physical states all of which will rapidly dispense a unitized amount of one or more selected fabric care agents to a wash and/or rinse bath solution during the laundering process under a variety of conditions. The invention also pertains to laundry kits that contain a variety of such articles and instructions concerning their use. Likewise, methods for preparing a customized laundry solution to obtain a specific fabric care benefit selected based on the user's personal preferences and/or the fabric care needs of the fabrics being laundered are also provided. Further, the present invention also concerns methods for assisting a consumer in identifying the unitized articles to be used in preparing a laundry solution that will impart desired fabric care benefits as well as merchandising displays for dispensing the articles, assembling customized laundry kits and instructing the consumer on the selection and use of laundry articles.

column12: DETERGENT COMPOSITION
column13: A detergent composition comprises or is prepared by combining an enzyme, a non-alkoxylated quaternary ammonium surfactant (non-AQA) and an AQA cationic surfactant of formula (I). R1R2N+ApR3(A'qR4) X- (I) R1 = substituted 8-18C alkyl, alkenyl, aryl, ether or glycidyl ether; R2 = 1-3C alkyl; R3, R4 = H, Me or Et; X = anion; A, A' = 1-4C alkoxy; p, q = 1-30. Also claimed are: (1) a method for removing soils and stains comprising contacting soils and stains with a detergent composition, or aqueous medium comprising the above detergent composition; and (2) a method for enhancing the deposition or substantivity of perfume or perfume ingredients onto fabrics or other surfaces comprising contacting the surfaces with perfume of perfume ingredient in the presence of compound (I).
